AM Lab Portfolio – Microsoft Entra ID

Hands-on identity and access management labs performed in a live Microsoft Entra ID tenant.

Labs Completed:

Lab 1 – SAML/SSO Configuration

	•	Created an enterprise application in Microsoft Entra ID
	•	Configured SAML-based single sign-on with custom Identifier and Reply URL
	•	Verified active token signing certificate and Federation Metadata XML

Lab 2 – User Provisioning & Deprovisioning

	•	Created user account (John Doe) following a new hire workflow
	•	Assigned user to enterprise application (IAM SAML Lab App)
	•	Removed application assignment and disabled account to simulate off-boarding

Environment: Microsoft Azure/Microsoft Entra ID P2 Trial 

Related Certifications: SC-300 Microsoft Identity and Access Administrator, CompTIA Security+

Lab 3 – Conditional Access

	•	Created a Conditional Access policy named “Require MFA – All Users”
	•	Scoped policy to all users and all cloud apps
	•	Set grant control to require multifactor authentication
	•	Enabled policy to enforced state

Lab 4 – Privileged Identity Management (PIM)

	•	Configured Security Reader role as an eligible assignment in PIM
	•	Activated the role just-in-time with a documented justification
	•	Verified activation in active assignments with time-bound access
	•	Demonstrated least-privilege access principles through JIT activation
	• Created and configured a time-bound Access Review for the Security Reader role with designated reviewer

	Lab 5 – PowerShell Identity Automation

	•	Wrote a PowerShell provisioning script (New-HireProvisioning.ps1) to automate new hire AD user creation, OU placement, security group assignment, and account enablement following least-privilege principles
	•	Wrote a PowerShell deprovisioning script (Remove-DepartingUser.ps1) to automate offboarding by disabling accounts, removing all group memberships, relocating users to a Disabled OU, and resetting passwords
	•	Scripts simulate a real enterprise IAM workflow covering the full identity lifecycle from onboarding to offboarding
